500|$|In rural Acadiana in {{southern}} Louisiana, gumbo {{is a central}} feature of Mardi Gras celebrations. [...] On Mardi Gras, local men wander {{from house to house}} and beg for gumbo ingredients in an event known as <b>courir</b> de Mardi Gras. Members of the local community then gather in a central location while the men cook the gumbo. [...] When it is ready, the group eats and dances until midnight, when Lent begins.|$|E
