50|$|The {{increased}} {{popularity of}} Cajun music and culture has {{also led to}} more nonlocal attention for the event. In 2011 the NPR show Snap Judgement did {{a series of interviews}} at one event and the <b>courir</b> was used in a story line by David Simon for his HBO series Treme In 2014 the HBO crime drama True Detective included images of <b>courir</b> participants and created a cult group whose roots lay partially in the rural Mardi Gras traditions.|$|E
